{
  "texts": [
    "Starting from a volume of events collected in the time range (t -1, t), a time surface is created and then enriched with memory channels built starting from events that were collected in the time range (0, t -1).",
    "The input of the network is then the concatenation of the three enriched time surfaces while the output is the pupil's position where x, y ∈ [0, 1].",
    "In this work k1 = 0.8, k2 = 0.6 and k3 = 0.4.",
    "The final FC block in the submitted solution includes two fully-connected layers with 220 and 2 neurons respectively.",
    "1 01saturates the argument between 0 and 1."
  ]
}